<module>
  <h>e</h>
  <p><g>e</g>
    <en>he, him, it</en> is the masculine singular <a href="?xx=nouns/personal_pronouns">personal
      pronoun</a>.</p>


  <section>
    <h>uses</h>
    <section id="sbj">
      <h>subject</h>
      <p><g>e</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>
      <p>Examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
        <en>be</en> – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha Calum sgìth – tha <m>e</m> ag obair gu trang anns an achadh.</gd>
            <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
          </li>
        </xl>
      </p>
      <p>Impersonal (pleonastic) examples – <xl>
          <li>
            <gd>Tha <m>e</m> fuar an diugh.</gd>
            <tr>It is cold today.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
          </li>
          <li>
            <gd>Chan eil <m>e</m> fuar an diugh.</gd>
            <tr>It is not cold today.</tr>
            <ref text="617">td. 11</ref>
          </li>
        </xl>
      </p>
    </section>
  </section>


